      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LET'S CAUSE KAOS (7) produced a moderate effort last time when seventh at this track over 600m behind Paw Danny (35.47) in a Grade 4/5. Has ability and can bounce back. ZIPPING TYRA (2) was prominent throughout when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when 5th and beaten 4.5 lengths at Ballarat (25.85). Should be in this for a long way. OFF THE BEER (5) produced a modest effort most recently when seventh at Healesville over 350m behind Electrojet (19.99) in a Grade 5 H. Warrants plenty of respect. COMPARE JOE (4) warrants respect although new to this track.",
